                  <div class="node odd full-node node-type-page" id="node-2">
                   <div class="inner">
                    <div class="content clearfix">
                     <h3>
                      <strong>
                       About Our Office
                      </strong>
                     </h3>
                     <p>
                      The Budget Office is a division of Business Affairs that reports directly to the Associate Vice Chancellor for Administration. The primary responsibility of the Budget Office is to allocate and monitor all budgeted funds appropriated by the North Carolina General Assembly as directed by the Board of Governors of the University of North Carolina System. All allocations are subject to mandates, regulations, and procedures established by the North Carolina Office of State Budget and Management in compliance with the State of North Carolina General Statutes, The University of North Carolina System-General Administration and the State Controller's Office. Monitoring certain Institutional Trust Funds is also included in the responsibilities.
                      <br/>
                      <br/>
                      Our Goal: To assist all areas of the University in developing and administering a comprehensive spending plan to support the total mission of Appalachian State University.
                     </p>
                     <h3>
                      <strong>
                       Location and Hours
                      </strong>
                     </h3>
                     <p>
                      Our office is located in the Office of the Vice Chancellor for Business Affairs, Third Floor, Suite 327,
                      <a href="http://maps.appstate.edu/campus-map/index.php?marker=68">
                       B.B. Dougherty Administration Building
                      </a>
                      .
                     </p>
                     <p>
                      Our hours are Monday - Friday, 8 a.m. to 5 p.m.  Please
                      <a href="contact">
                       contact us
                      </a>
                      for more information.
                     </p>
                     <h3>
                     </h3>
                     <h3>
                     </h3>
                    </div>
